    • Field Detail

      • ACTION_NEXT

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_NEXT
        Broadcast Action: NEXT
        "com.pax.us.pay.ui.NEXT"

        For a entry (Activity Action), when you get the required OUTPUT ready,
        you need send a broadcast to BroadPOS (the caller),
        Example:
        BroadPOS start the activity TextEntry.ACTION_ENTER_AMOUNT which implemented in your app,
        after input done, you send a broadcast like this: 

             Bundle bundle = new Bundle();
     bundle.putLong(EntryRequest.PARAM_AMOUNT,amount);
     bundle.putStringExtra(EntryRequest.PARAM_ACTION,TextEntry.ACTION_ENTER_AMOUNT);
     Intent intent = new Intent();
     intent.setPackage(broadPOSPackage); //broadPOSPackage is from EntryExtraData.PARAM_PACKAGE
     intent.setAction(EntryRequest.ACTION_NEXT);
     intent.putExtras(bundle);
     context.sendBroadcast(intent);

        For some actions which have no required outputs, like ConfirmationEntry.ACTION_DISPLAY_QR_CODE_RECEIPT, you can send NEXT by this way: 

             Intent intent = new Intent();
     intent.setPackage(broadPOSPackage); //broadPOSPackage is from EntryExtraData.PARAM_PACKAGE
     intent.setAction(EntryRequest.ACTION_NEXT);
     context.sendBroadcast(intent);
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_ABORT

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_ABORT
        Broadcast Action: ABORT
        "com.pax.us.pay.ui.ABORT"

        When you try to abort the transaction, you can send broadcast to BroadPOS.
        Example: try to abort action TextEntry.ACTION_ENTER_AMOUNT: 

             Bundle bundle = new Bundle();
     bundle.putStringExtra(EntryRequest.PARAM_ACTION,TextEntry.ACTION_ENTER_AMOUNT);
     Intent intent = new Intent();
     intent.setPackage(broadPOSPackage); //broadPOSPackage is from EntryExtraData.PARAM_PACKAGE
     intent.setAction(EntryRequest.ACTION_ABORT);
     intent.putExtras(bundle);
     context.sendBroadcast(intent);

      • ACTION_SECURITY_AREA

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_SECURITY_AREA
        Broadcast Action: Set Secure Area
        "com.pax.us.pay.ui.SECURITY_AREA"

        For SecurityEntry, you need tell BroadPOS about your input box after UI layout is ready.
        Then BroadPOS could show security widget on specific position.
        general you can do it on windows focused or on global layout done.

        Example Code: 
             Bundle bundle = new Bundle();
     bundle.putInt(EntryRequest.PARAM_X, x);
     bundle.putInt(EntryRequest.PARAM_Y, y);
     bundle.putInt(EntryRequest.PARAM_WIDTH, width);
     bundle.putInt(EntryRequest.PARAM_HEIGHT, height);
     bundle.putInt(EntryRequest.PARAM_FONT_SIZE, fontSize);
     bundle.putString(EntryRequest.PARAM_FOCUSABLE, focusAble);
     bundle.putString(EntryRequest.PARAM_HINT, hint);
     bundle.putString(EntryRequest.PARAM_COLOR, fontColor);
     Intent intent = new Intent();
     intent.setPackage(broadPOSPackage); //broadPOSPackage is from EntryExtraData.PARAM_PACKAGE
     intent.putExtras(bundle);
     intent.setAction(EntryRequest.ACTION_SECURITY_AREA);
     context.sendBroadcast(intent);

        ExtraData: PARAM_X - is X coordinate of input box
        Type: Integer
        Unit: pixel

        ExtraData: PARAM_Y - is Y coordinate of input box
        Type: Integer
        Unit: pixel

        ExtraData: PARAM_WIDTH - is width of input box
        Type: Integer
        Unit: pixel

        ExtraData: PARAM_HEIGHT - is height of input box
        Type: Integer
        Unit: pixel

        ExtraData: PARAM_FONT_SIZE - is font size of input box
        Type: Integer
        Unit: scaled pixel

        ExtraData: PARAM_FOCUSABLE - Optional
        Type: Boolean
        TRUE is focusable.

        ExtraData: PARAM_HINT - Optional
        Type: String

        ExtraData: PARAM_COLOR - Optional
        Type : String
        Format: ARGB
        Example:
        "ffffffff" which represent the opaque white color.
        "cc00ff00" which means the green color with 20% transparent.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_SET_PIN_KEY_LAYOUT

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_SET_PIN_KEY_LAYOUT
        Broadcast Action: Set Pin Pad Layout
        "com.pax.us.pay.ui.SET_PIN_LAYOUT"

        For SecurityEntry.ACTION_ENTER_PIN Only
        Need to be sent before ACTION_SECURITY_AREA
        You can send this broadcast to BroadPOS if you prefer your PIN PAD layout.

        Example Code: 
             Intent intent = new Intent();
     intent.setPackage(broadPOSPackage); //broadPOSPackage is from EntryExtraData.PARAM_PACKAGE
     intent.setAction(EntryRequest.ACTION_SET_PIN_KEY_LAYOUT);
     intent.putExtra(PARAM_KEY_0, new Rect(left0, top0, right0, bottom0); // location is from getLocationOnScreen
     ...
     ...
     intent.putExtra(PARAM_KEY_CANCEL, new Rect(leftCancel, topCancel, rightCancel, bottomCancel);
     context.sendBroadcast(intent);

        ExtraData: PARAM_KEY_0 -
        Type: android.graphics.Rect

        ExtraData: PARAM_KEY_1 -
        Type: android.graphics.Rect

        ExtraData: PARAM_KEY_2 -
        Type: android.graphics.Rect

        ExtraData: PARAM_KEY_3 -
        Type: android.graphics.Rect

        ExtraData: PARAM_KEY_4 -
        Type: android.graphics.Rect

        ExtraData: PARAM_KEY_5 -
        Type: android.graphics.Rect

      • ACTION_START_SCAN

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_START_SCAN
        Broadcast Action: Start QR Code Scan
        "com.pax.us.pay.ui.START_SCAN"

        Used for SecurityEntry.ACTION_INPUT_ACCOUNT
        If user click the Start Scan button on your input account UI, you can tell BroadPOS to start scan.

        Example Code: 
             Intent intent = new Intent(EntryRequest.ACTION_START_SCAN);
     intent.setPackage(broadPOSPackage); //broadPOSPackage is from EntryExtraData.PARAM_PACKAGE
     context.sendBroadcast(intent);
